<NomaiObject>
	<TextBlock>
		<ID>1</ID>
		<Text>CONOY: What have we learned thus far in our search for the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye of the universe</color>]]>?</Text>
	</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock>
		<ID>2</ID>
		<ParentID>1</ParentID>
		<Text>PLUME: Those of us on the <![CDATA[<color=orange>Vessel</color>]]> originally followed the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye</color>]]>’s signal to this star system, but we were unable to warp to the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye</color>]]> itself.</Text>
	</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock>
		<ID>3</ID>
		<ParentID>2</ParentID>
		<Text>PRIVET: The locator we built on the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Attlerock</color>]]> and the new, more sensitive locator we built here were both unable to detect any trace of the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye</color>]]>’s signal.</Text>
	</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock>
		<ID>4</ID>
		<ParentID>3</ParentID>
		<Text>AVENS: Hypothesis: The <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye</color>]]> has stopped emitting its signal.</Text>
	</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock>
		<ID>5</ID>
		<ParentID>3</ParentID>
		<Text>CASSAVA: Suppose the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye</color>]]> doesn’t wish to be found.</Text>
	</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock>
		<ID>6</ID>
		<ParentID>5</ParentID>
		<Text>PLUME: Cassava, how can you suggest that? The <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye</color>]]>’s signal called out to summon us to this star system!</Text>
	</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock>
		<ID>7</ID>
		<ParentID>6</ParentID>
		<Text>CASSAVA: I’m aware; I grew up hearing the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye</color>]]>’s story. Yet we’re no closer to finding it than you were when you first arrived here.</Text>
	</TextBlock>
		<TextBlock>
		<ID>8</ID>
		<ParentID>1</ParentID>
		<Text>MALLOW: Based on our knowledge of the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Quantum Moon</color>]]>, we believe the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye</color>]]> is in orbit around this star system’s <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>sun</color>]]>. This would mean the <![CDATA[<color=lightblue>Eye</color>]]> is located within a finite (albeit enormous) range.</Text>
	</TextBlock>

